<br>
Also taunting a mob off a shaman after he cast a slow then letting him cast another spell with you doing nothing is not a good way to test this. Taunt puts you at the top of the hate list but no one knows by how much. Let's say it's by one point over the highest person already on the list. Now lets say every mob has a base hate factor on any spell action a player makes towards it. Sure the spell didn't go through, but the mob could have built hate just on the fact that player did cast a spell against it.<br>
